---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pool Builders Robina | Family Pools, Resurfacing | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Swimming pool builders for Robina — Robina Quays / Woods estate fibreglass family pools, 1990s–2000s pool resurface, salt-rated equipment upgrades. QBCC-licensed.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/robina/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Robina &middot; Robina Quays &middot; Robina Woods &middot; Varsity Lakes</span>
      <h1>Pool builders &amp; resurfacers in <span class="accent">Robina</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Robina is master-planned family country. Late-1980s through 2010s build
        wave, mostly two-storey brick homes on 500&ndash;800m&sup2; blocks,
        family-led design briefs. About 60% of our local work is the
        first-resurface generation hitting now; the other 40% is new fibreglass
        installs in newer pockets and the occasional concrete-pool upgrade.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Robina</span>
      <h2>The Robina pool story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>First-resurface generation.</h3>
        <p>
          Robina&rsquo;s peak build wave was 1990&ndash;2008. That makes the
          original pool stock 18&ndash;36 years old now &mdash; right in the
          <strong>first resurface window</strong> for the older end of the wave.
          The typical Robina pool we see in 2026 is an 8m&times;4m rectangular
          concrete pool with a tired pebble interior, salt-chlorinator system
          on its 3rd or 4th cell, and original 1990s solar heating that&rsquo;s
          long since failed. Resurface + equipment modernisation is the
          standard package: $25K&ndash;$45K all-in, vs $80K&ndash;$120K for a
          full pool replacement.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Family-led design briefs.</h3>
        <p>
          The conversation here is almost always &ldquo;safe for the kids,
          easy to maintain, big enough for swimming.&rdquo; That points to:
          <strong>large baja / sun-deck step</strong> for toddlers and dogs,
          rounded coping (no sharp corners), self-cleaning return jets,
          variable-speed pump (quieter and 50% less energy), salt chlorinator
          rather than chlorine handling, and a robotic cleaner to take the
          weekly pool-vac off the parents&rsquo; chores. Whole-of-life pool
          ownership cost on a properly-spec&rsquo;d new install: $1,200&ndash;$1,800/yr
          power + chemicals on a Robina-typical 8m pool.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Robina Woods / Robina Quays canal-edge work.</h3>
        <p>
          Robina Quays and parts of Robina Woods have <strong>man-made lake and
          canal frontage</strong>. These pools sit close to the lake &mdash; sometimes
          with a knife-edge wall facing the water. Council requires a structural
          engineer&rsquo;s certificate for any pool within 3m of a lake/canal
          retaining wall (load transfer concerns). We&rsquo;ve done a dozen of
          these &mdash; the engineering adds $4K&ndash;$8K but is non-negotiable.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Glass-fence integration with existing landscape.</h3>
        <p>
          Robina pool fencing is almost always retrofitted to an existing landscape:
          established palms, paving runs that pre-date the pool, decked alfresco
          attached to the house. We design the glass fence panels and gate
          placement to <strong>follow the existing paving lines</strong> rather
          than cutting them up &mdash; means the resurface + fence project
          finishes looking integrated rather than &ldquo;new fence dropped on top.&rdquo;
          Cross-reference: pool safety certificate (Form 23) compliance is
          essential at any sale event in Robina.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Robina jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1990s 8m&times;4m pool full resurface to Quartzon + new salt chlorinator + heat pump ($30K&ndash;$45K)</li>
          <li>New fibreglass 7m family pool with paving surround ($55K&ndash;$72K turnkey)</li>
          <li>Robina Quays lake-edge concrete pool with structural engineering ($110K&ndash;$160K)</li>
          <li>Pre-sale pool safety certificate remediation + light cosmetic refresh ($8K&ndash;$15K)</li>
          <li>Variable-speed pump retrofit on tired single-speed system (saves $400&ndash;$800/yr in power)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mermaid-beach/">Mermaid Beach</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/burleigh-heads/">Burleigh Heads</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/mudgeeraba/">Mudgeeraba</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/helensvale/">Helensvale</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-gold-coast/">All City of Gold Coast</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Robina on-site quote.</h2>
        <p>First-resurface assessment. Family-led design. Pre-sale Form 23 remediation done quickly.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
